Dialogue: 10,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.47,Caption,,0,0,0,,Four. Both the main and backup units ran\Nidentical
Dialogue: 10,0:00:03.47,0:00:07.33,Caption,,0,0,0,,software. So the redundancy — the whole\Npoint of having
Dialogue: 10,0:00:07.33,0:00:11.19,Caption,,0,0,0,,two — was an illusion. A backup only\Nhelps if
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.19,0:00:15.05,Caption,,0,0,0,,it can fail in a different way. This one\Nwas
Dialogue: 10,0:00:15.05,0:00:18.91,Caption,,0,0,0,,guaranteed to fail in exactly the same\Nway, at exactly
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.07,Caption,,0,0,0,,the same instant.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:20.41,0:00:23.74,Caption,,0,0,0,,Put those together and the shape of it\Nis clear.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:23.74,0:00:27.07,Caption,,0,0,0,,This wasn't the story of a bad\Nprogrammer. It was
Dialogue: 10,0:00:27.07,0:00:30.40,Caption,,0,0,0,,the story of a good assumption that\Nquietly stopped being
Dialogue: 10,0:00:30.40,0:00:33.73,Caption,,0,0,0,,true — and a system with no one left to
Dialogue: 10,0:00:33.73,0:00:34.06,Caption,,0,0,0,,notice.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:34.40,0:00:38.17,Caption,,0,0,0,,The code wasn't wrong for Ariane 4. It\Nwas wrong
Dialogue: 10,0:00:38.17,0:00:41.94,Caption,,0,0,0,,for the rocket it was actually bolted\Nto. And nobody
Dialogue: 10,0:00:41.94,0:00:45.32,Caption,,0,0,0,,had asked the question, because it had\Nnever needed
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.32,0:00:45.70,Caption,,0,0,0,,asking.
